13... g6 14. Bxf6
{ Continuing the plan and a final important move to know. Please do not fall for the sneaky  14.Bxg6??  Qe7!  when there's just no way for White not to lose a piece. }
14... Nxf6 15. Qe2
{ White enjoy a pleasant edge, in part due having the safer king, as well as the hole on e5. After Nf3 and Rad1, it may be possible to increase the pressure with c2-c4 or even to attack with a combination of Ne5 and Qe1-g3. }
