13... Nxe5 14. fxe5 Ne4 15. a4
{ Richard has long quite liked this prophylactic advance.   15.c4  Nxd2  16.Qxd2  and  @@StartFEN@@2r2rk1/pbq1bppp/1p2p3/3pP3/3Pn3/PP1B4/1BPNQ1PP/R4RK1 w - - 1 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Rae1  are decent alternatives.  The text move rules out ...b5, as White did in Bronnikov-Shubin, correspondence 2012. White may next go Nf3 and c2-c4 or even Bxe4!? dxe4; c4 followed by aiming to round up the straggler on e4. }
