{ Continuing our favourite pattern of development and now Black usually follows suit and houses the king too. }
8... O-O 9. Nbd2
{ Continuing our favourite pattern of development and once again refusing to fear  9...Nb4  ,  since after  10.Be2  the bishop will be quick to return to d3 following a2-a3 @@StartBracket@@or even c2-c3@@EndBracket@@. If Black now does something slow, White may well rule out any annoying ...Nb4 notion with 10. a3 and then expand with Ne5, whether before or after Qe2. }
