{ The other capture is also rather good. In both cases a pin on the e-file will prove near fatal for Black. }
12... Bxe5 13. Re1
{ Now  13...Ng4  is simply met by  14.h3  and even the more radical knight moves don't come close to saving Black. }
13... Ne4 14. Nxe4
{ Not the only good move, but perhaps the strongest. White simply wants to go two pawns to the good after  14...dxe4  15.Rxe4  f6  16.Nxe5  fxe5  17.Qe2  ,  and is quite happy to dangle the rook on a1 before Black: }
14... Bxa1 15. Neg5
{ Even stronger than  15.Nc3  Qxa3  16.Qxa1  Qxa1  17.Rxa1  with a huge advantage in the endgame. }
15... Qxa3 16. Bxh7+ Kh8 17. Ne5
{ the attack is simply a winner with Qh5 such a threat and  17...g6  poleaxed by  18.Bxg6!  . }
