12... Be6 13. c5
{ Seizing space and agreeing to force the pace. It's also very possible to maintain the tension and a small edge with  13.Rc1!?  when Ng5 might even become an idea. }
13... Bc7 14. b5
{ Now  14...Na5?  15.Nxe5  Qxc5  16.Nef3  followed by Rc1 and Qa4 would simply leave Black suffering from an IQP and offside knight, so he too should force the pace: }
14... e4 15. bxc6 exf3 16. Nxf3 bxc6 17. Qc2
