{ Yet more simple chess. White is now ready to complete development with Qe2 and Rac1, while an immediate threat is  11.c5!  and Re1 or Qe2, clamping down on the e5-square and leaving Black cramped. We also don't need to fear any notion of an IQP on d4: }
10... dxc4 11. Nxc4
{ This is why and appears a better choice than  11.bxc4  . White not only threatens to bag the two bishops, but is ready to expand with Nfe5 and Black is left looking a little cramped. }
11... Be7 12. Rc1 Qd8 13. Nfe5
{ Despite the IQP, White enjoyed a definite pull here in Salter-Plesec, European Senior Championship, Mali Losinj 2019, with Qf3 on the way, followed likely by Rfe1 and then maybe some combination of Qh3 and bringing one of the knights to g4. }
