{ Taking firm control of e5, while also encouraging Black to slide his queen to c7. Should Black proceed very slowly then White may just go 11. Qe2 and 12. Rf3 or even perhaps 11. Qf3 and 12. g4. }
10... Rc8 11. Rf3
{ Heading straight for h3. 11. Qe2 is also very possible, but do note that here  11.Nxd7!?  Nxd7!  12.dxc5  Bxc5!  13.Bxh7+  leads to no more than a draw after  13...Kxh7  14.Qh5+  Kg8  15.Bxg7  f5!  . Instead, with the direct rook lift we do threaten to take on d7, c5 and then h7. }
