Ne4 13. Bxd4
{ Once again, White keeps both bishops in the thick of the action and would now love to get @@StartFEN@@2rq1rk1/pb1n1ppp/1p1bp3/3pN3/3BnP2/1P1BP2R/P1PN2PP/R2Q2K1 w - - 0 13@@EndFEN@@  14.Nxd7  Qxd7  15.Qh5  in. }
13... Nxe5 14. fxe5 Bc5 15. Qe2
{ Black has defended solidly, but we would still slightly prefer to take White, who has the more effective light-squared bishop. Clearly Rf1 is on the way, any exchange on d4 may lead to Black coming under pressure on e4 and ...f5 can always be met by a line-opening exf6. }
