7... c5 8. dxc5
{ A fearless exchange and clearly now both  8...O-O?  9.c6   and  8...Qa5?  9.b4  wouldn't be good news for Black. }
8... Ne4 9. Nd4
{ Simple chess, although  9.Nbd2!?  is a pretty tempting exchange sacrifice. Now  @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pp1n1pbp/4p1p1/2Pp4/3Nn3/BP1BP3/P1P2PPP/RN1Q1RK1 b kq - 2 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Ndxc5?  10.f3  Nxd3  11.fxe4!  would seize the initiative, so Black should recapture the other way: }
9... Nexc5 10. Bb5
{ Pinning so that  10...O-O?  11.Bxd7  would cost Black the exchange. } 10...
Qb6 11. c4
{ With Nc3 to follow White has seized the initiative and will be able to increase the pressure by playing against d5 or with a timely Na4. }
