4... b6 5. b3
{ We'll now take a look at a solid line from Black where he mirrors White with a queenside fianchetto and holds back on a central challenge with ...c5. Note though that on pretty much every move Black can go ...c5 if he prefers when play is extremely likely to transpose back into a line we considered in Theory One, Two or Three, depending on where the bishop on f8 and knight on b8 are developed to.   For our part, standard Colle-Zukertort development with Bb2, O-O and Nbd2 is the main plan, while also keeping an eye on an early c2-c4 break should Black be a little ambitious with an early ...Ne4 or ...Ba6. }
5... Bb7 6. Bb2
{ Increasing the grip on e5 and now Black's most solid approach sees him setting up with ...Nbd7 and ...Be7. }
6... Nbd7 7. O-O
{ Standard stuff from White and now 7...Be7 is the most annoying move to face, but is by no means forced. }
7... Be7 8. Nbd2
{ The first stage of development is complete and will Black now house his king or try something more ambitious? The latter is, perhaps unsurprisingly, recommended by Benjamin Gledura on his Lifetime Repertoires: Gledura's Queen's Gambit Accepted. }
8... Ne4 9. c4
{ Again, the best response to the invasion of e4, in contrast to which  9.Ne5  Nxe5!  10.dxe5  O-O  is just extremely solid for Black. We are now ready to increase the pressure against e4 and also begin to generate some pressure down the c-file with Qc2. }
9... O-O 10. Qc2 Nxd2 11. Nxd2
{ White should recapture and not fall for the unfavourable  11.Bxh7+  Kh8  12.Nxd2  g6!  .   As we saw back at the start of the course, White might now meet  11...Nf6  with the cramping  12.c5!?   And  11...g6  12.Rad1  would centralise nicely ahead of breaking with e3-e4, and all the while we're hoping Black will still be seduced by Stonewall ideas. }
11... f5 12. cxd5
{ Now  12...exd5  13.Bxf5  simply picks off a pawn and neither is the other recapture a bed of roses for Black. }
12... Bxd5 13. e4 fxe4 14. Nxe4
{ The weaknesses of e6 and h7 are much more important than that of the IQP. White simply wants to increase the pressure with Nc3, Rae1 and possibly even then Re3. }
