7... Nc6 8. O-O { Stepping out of the pin. } 8... Bd6 9. Re1 O-O 10. Ne5
{ White beats Black to using the e5-square and may well now complete development not with Bb2, but Bf4 and Qe2, thereby leaving Black with a potentially problematic light-squared bishop unless he drops the queen back to c7, but then White will complete development with Nd2-f3. }
