9... c6 10. c4 { White strives to pressure d5 and open lines after all. } 10...
exd4 11. exd4 dxc4 12. O-O
{ This is a rather unusual type of Catalan, but you have to quite like the unopposed bishop on g2. Now Re1+ will follow or just Nxc4 and do note that ...Nb6; Nxc4 will regain the pawn in any case thanks to the check on e2. }
