14... c4 15. Bc3
{ 15.Qc2  has been somewhat more common, but we rather liked the principled text, which Alireza Firouzja unfurled in Firouzja-So, Skilling @@StartBracket@@rapid@@EndBracket@@ 2020.   White is happy to gambit h2 to get his queenside pawns well down the board.   Play continued: @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/2qn1ppp/3bpn2/1P1p4/P1p5/2B1PN2/3N1PPP/R2Q1RK1 b - - 1 15@@EndFEN@@  15...e5  16.a5!  e4  17.b6  Qb8  18.Nd4  Bxh2+  19.Kh1  Taking stock after the forcing sequence, we find White threatening both Nc6 and g2-g3.   The engines confirm that there should be more than enough compensation, with one other important idea:  19...Be5  20.f4!  exf3  21.Qxf3  White certainly isn't getting mated here as Black finds himself under pressure right across the board, with Qh3 followed by N2f3 one good idea, e3-e4 another. }
