3... Bf5 4. c4
{ Retreating to f5 is likely to be the choice of a stronger player, but Black is still faced with definite problems to solve after this central break.  White would now be delighted to net the bishop-pair after all following  4...Bxb1  5.Rxb1  and meanwhile frees a path for his queen to exploit the absence of the bishop on c8.   Yes, Qb3 is already quite a threat and even Qa4@@StartBracket@@+@@EndBracket@@ may prove useful, especially in the event of  4...Nc6?!  5.Qa4  pinning. }
