4... Qc8 5. c4
{ With Black having taken steps to deal with  5.Qh3  and go  5.Qb5+  c6  we switch back to undermining d5 and would now be delighted to take over the centre after  @@StartFEN@@rnq1kbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3pN2b/2PP4/3Q4/PP2PPPP/RNB1KB1R b KQkq c3 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5...dxc4  6.Qxc4  followed by Nc3 and e2-e4. }
