[SetUp "1"]

10... Ne4
{ Black has either blundered or is going for a pawn-sacrifice. What's the best path forward? }
11. Nxe4
{ White should not be afraid; he's capturing first and will win a pawn: } 11...
Nxe5 12. Nxc5 Nxd3 13. Nxd3
{ Black's bishops don't offer him enough for a pawn. Rather than open up the unopposed bishop on b7 with c2-c4, White likely does better to aim for f4-f5 or even a2-a4 and Ra3 to deprive Black of the bishop-pair. }
