[SetUp "1"]

21... Bd6
{ We've seen it over and over, but it goes to show how even strong players will allow such tactics. Note this game saw the classic Colle with c3 instead of b3, but the point is both bishops are working along great diagonals. }
22. Bxh7+ { Exposing the lone king. } 22... Kxh7 23. Qh5+ Kg8 24. Bxg7
{ The notorious double-bishop sacrifice. Only attempt this if your rook has a clear path to the g or h-files. }
24... Kxg7 25. Qg5+ Kh7 26. Rd4 Bh2+ 27. Kh1 Qf4 28. Rxf4
{ Black was forced to cede the queen and with it the game.   Koltanowski, G. vs. Defosse, M. 1936 }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
