[SetUp "1"]

14... Qd7
{ If White is allowed the f5 break in such a position, what is the most decisive way forward? }
15. f6
{ Clearly Black was ready to recapture with his queen on e6, but Bu must have been delighted to be allowed to carry out White's other threat. Already it's looking extremely unlikely that the black king will survive. }
15... Bd8 16. Qg4 Ng6 17. h4
{ Black has done his best to avoid fatally weakening his dark squares on the kingside, but has absolutely no defence to the arrival of Harry.   Bu Xiangzhi vs. Thorhallsson, T. Reykjavik Rapid, 2013 }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
