[SetUp "1"]

17... Nh7
{ Once again - the knight has just been provoked to a passive role away from its home on f6. How did Yusupov break through? }
18. Qxh5 { Taking advantage of the pin on the g6 pawn. } 18... Bxg5 19. Bxg6
{ The only move, maintaining the initiative and busting open the kingside. }
19... f6 20. f4 Qg7 21. fxg5 Nxg5 22. h4 Ne4 23. Bxe4 dxe4 24. Rf4
{ Rg4 is coming.  Yusupov, A. vs. Scheeren, Peter, 1983 } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Thematic Tactic #19 "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "2r2rk1/3qbp2/p1b1pnp1/1p1pB1Np/5PPQ/1P1BP3/P1P4P/3R1RK1 b - - 0 20"]
[SetUp "1"]

20... Nxg4 { Too many pieces swarming the black king. How to end it? } 21. Qxh5
{ It's mate in two. } 21... gxh5 22. Bh7# { Checkmate! } *

